HEADWORD: Estrepement
<hw>Es*trepe"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF., damage,
waste.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A destructive kind of waste,
committed by a tenant for life, in lands, woods, or houses.</def>
<rj><au>Cowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
